{
  "texts": [
    "expðW t 2;l À W t 1;l Þ.",
    "We define W t;l as the average random effect in language l over all users u active at time point t. This captures the averaged change in expected tweeting activity due to a change in average tweeting intensity of the active users, when controlling for behavioural changes.",
    "Language modelling.",
    "To model users' pairwise language probability, we refrain from a multinomial modelling strategy, as even with a weekly setup our dataset is particularly large.",
    "(To the best of our knowledge, a package with a parallel estimation routine for large datasets that can fit a GAMM for a multinomial distribution does not exist.)"
  ]
}